isn't politics.

02:50.000 --> 02:55.000
When your last film,
Salo, will be released,

02:55.000 --> 02:58.000
will you scandalize again?

03:01.760 --> 03:04.843
I think to scandalize
is a right,

03:05.040 --> 03:07.247
to be scandalized is a pleasure,

03:07.440 --> 03:10.444
and those who refuse to be
scandalized are moralists.

03:10.640 --> 03:11.801
the so called moralists.

03:22.200 --> 03:25.801
Why aren't you a
militant anymore?

03:26.000 --> 03:27.445
What do you mean?

03:28.000 --> 03:29.445
You are not a political
militant anymore.

03:30.120 --> 03:32.327
I am more than ever.

03:35.120 --> 03:39.327
Are you nostalgic of the period in which
people insulted you in the streets?

03:39.760 --> 03:41.683
They're still insulting me.

03:41.900 --> 03:44.900
Does it provoke in you
a certain pleasure?

03:46.800 --> 03:49.280
I don't deny it

03:49.480 --> 03:51.369
since I'm not a moralist.

03:52.480 --> 03:54.369
What is the profession
you prefer?

03:54.480 --> 04:01.369
Poet? Writer? Scenarist? Actor?
Critic? Director?

04:05.480 --> 04:09.369
In my passport, I simply
report: "writer".

05:32.920 --> 05:34.684
Dear Alberto

05:34.880 --> 05:37.406
I send you this

05:37.600 --> 05:39.045
so that you can give me advice.

05:39.240 --> 05:41.004
It's a novel

05:41.200 --> 05:44.044
but it's not written
like true novels are:

05:44.240 --> 05:47.767
its terminology is the
one used in essays,

05:47.960 --> 05:49.883
in some newspaper articles,

05:50.080 --> 05:50.922
in reviews,

05:51.120 --> 05:53.771
in private letters
or even in poetry.

05:55.120 --> 05:57.566
This is the advice
I ask from you:

05:57.760 --> 06:00.730
is what I've written enough,

06:00.920 --> 06:05.289
in order to decently and poetically
say what I wanted to say?

06:13.240 --> 06:16.528
I'd like you to consider,
before advising me

06:16.720 --> 06:20.202
that the protagonist of
this novel is whoever he is

06:20.400 --> 06:23.847
and, analogies between his
story and mine aside,

06:24.040 --> 06:26.486
he disgusts me.

06:37.240 --> 06:40.926
This novel is of no use
to my life anymore..

06:41.120 --> 06:46.968
It is not a proclamation. It
is the preamble to a testament

06:47.160 --> 06:52.041
the testimony of that little of
knowledge that a man has gathered,

06:52.240 --> 06:56.962
a totally different knowledge from
what he had expected it to be.

06:57.160 --> 06:58.844
or wondered.

07:37.400 --> 07:38.640
Love.

07:45.280 --> 07:46.327
Go.

07:52.280 --> 07:53.850
Good.

08:02.440 --> 08:06.411
Good. Come on..

08:07.880 --> 08:09.120
Yes...

10:00.480 --> 10:03.723
Ninni.. Pieruti

10:15.360 --> 10:16.600
Mom.

10:16.800 --> 10:21.601
You're back... We've been so
far away one from another.

10:27.320 --> 10:29.288
I'm getting up, mom.

12:56.800 --> 12:57.926
Hi Pieruti.

12:58.120 --> 12:59.531
Hi Graziella.

12:59.720 --> 13:00.801
How did the trip go?

13:01.000 --> 13:01.967
It went well, thanks.

13:15.240 --> 13:20.007
Listen Graziella... you have
to read Sciascia's last novel,

13:20.200 --> 13:22.726
you can take it from my desk

13:22.920 --> 13:25.366
it's a really important book.

13:25.560 --> 13:27.244
Thank you, I'll read it.

13:30.280 --> 13:32.931
Carlo Levi called to say hi.

13:33.120 --> 13:33.689
Yes.

13:33.880 --> 13:35.484
La Stampa's editor would
like you to call him back.

13:35.680 --> 13:36.647
Ok.

13:36.840 --> 13:40.128
Ah, I've copied your
speech for the radicals'

13:40.320 --> 13:42.084
meeting and I've put
it on your desk.

13:42.280 --> 13:43.725
That's good, thanks.

15:15.680 --> 15:18.843
Carlo was not the only
powerful individual

15:19.040 --> 15:21.202
to adapt to such
an official feast,

15:22.880 --> 15:24.848
a destination for opportunists,

15:25.040 --> 15:25.882
for snobs,

15:26.080 --> 15:27.241
for background actors,

15:27.440 --> 15:30.364
for officials and
bureaucrats with ladies.

15:30.560 --> 15:35.088
And he wasn't the only one who had
to make the best of a bad situation.

15:35.280 --> 15:39.968
At the center, unmoved mover,
was the Head of State..

15:40.160 --> 15:44.484
Even during the
democracy process

15:44.680 --> 15:47.604
the “holy game of kings” kept being
played, and the ritualistic life

15:47.800 --> 15:50.929
of royalty is still well spread
among the bourgeoisie...

15:51.120 --> 15:54.522
Meanwhile all around Carlo,

15:54.720 --> 15:57.326
who just entered,
there was pure chaos.

15:59.440 --> 16:01.966
I've been attacked by
certain journalists lately,

16:02.160 --> 16:04.481
journalists related to ENI

16:04.680 --> 16:10.323
So many disappointments. That's
why I had to do it my way.

16:32.480 --> 16:35.165
I tell you, tell the Americans

16:35.360 --> 16:38.250
that the government has no intention
whatsoever of taxing oil.

16:38.440 --> 16:39.248
Sure, sure, sure.

16:40.800 --> 16:43.804
Vincenzo Cazzaniga
is highly esteemed

16:44.000 --> 16:46.048
in the very Vatican Bank.

16:46.240 --> 16:47.969
The Agnellis get
their money back

16:48.160 --> 16:49.366
through the Vatican Bank.

16:49.560 --> 16:50.083
Sure.

16:52.120 --> 16:55.249
To us Andreotti and honesty
are the same thing.

16:55.440 --> 16:57.920
Because if he says
that those bombs in

16:58.120 --> 16:59.360
Milan are not our problem,

16:59.560 --> 17:01.642
it means that they're not.

17:01.840 --> 17:03.171
Well then, we adapt

17:03.360 --> 17:04.599
we adapt to all this.

17:05.000 --> 17:06.365
OK, that's right.

17:12.040 --> 17:15.964
Narrative, as you
well know, is dead.

17:16.160 --> 17:19.607
We're mourning it.

17:22.560 --> 17:25.530
Mine is not a tale,
but a metaphor.

17:28.280 --> 17:32.171
The meaning of this metaphor
is the relationship between

17:32.360 --> 17:34.966
an artist and what he
creates and shapes.

