18:51.960 --> 18:54.691
Andrea Fago, or
the "eating man",

18:54.880 --> 18:59.204
took as usually the
Alitalia DC9 flight,

18:59.400 --> 19:02.244
on a calm spring afternoon,

19:02.440 --> 19:05.364
a flight ought to
land on Cape Town.

19:12.800 --> 19:14.404
- There you go.
- Thanks..

19:19.280 --> 19:20.725
What's your name, miss?

19:20.920 --> 19:21.807
Caterina.

19:22.000 --> 19:23.729
Caterina.

19:23.920 --> 19:26.366
At what time we're
done, Caterina?

19:26.560 --> 19:27.925
We land at 12.

19:28.120 --> 19:31.090
And are you going to
have lunch with someone?

19:31.280 --> 19:31.803
No.

19:32.000 --> 19:32.842
May I invite you?

19:33.040 --> 19:34.007
Why not?

19:42.920 --> 19:47.642
Those would be some hours of
quite and beautiful travel.

19:47.840 --> 19:52.323
First of all Egypt,

19:52.520 --> 19:54.409
and its Nile,

19:56.120 --> 19:58.282
and its green trees,

19:58.480 --> 20:01.689
and its palms and

20:01.880 --> 20:05.885
the cornfields, and the
dark okra villages.

20:06.200 --> 20:09.602
After that Sudan,

20:09.800 --> 20:14.169
and its never-ending
southern desert,

20:14.360 --> 20:16.044
so wonderfully pink.

20:19.680 --> 20:22.604
I would like to insist
that this desert's pink is

20:22.800 --> 20:23.961
really something:

20:24.160 --> 20:28.165
but it's even more
impressive its vastness.

20:28.360 --> 20:32.365
It never ends and never changes,

20:32.560 --> 20:37.122
from Khartoum to Rudolph Lake.

20:37.320 --> 20:41.086
what gives a feeling of
terror to this desert

20:41.280 --> 20:45.524
though is the fact that
it is not a desert,

20:45.720 --> 20:51.841
but a huge hollow country,
forgotten by both God and man.

20:52.040 --> 20:54.247
Well, this was the desert

20:54.440 --> 20:56.681
in which the Alitalia
DC9 crashed.

21:15.880 --> 21:20.442
All that I'm going to tell
you was not displayed

21:20.640 --> 21:25.601
in this world's theatre
but in my head's.

21:25.800 --> 21:29.361
It took not place in
the space of reality,

21:29.560 --> 21:32.006
but in the one of
my imagination.

21:32.200 --> 21:37.240
And eventually, it played out not
according to the contradictory rules

21:37.440 --> 21:41.490
of the game of the existence,
but it did according to the

21:41.680 --> 21:44.251
contradictory rules of
the game of my reason.

22:08.360 --> 22:12.888
Andrea Fago watched those men
who where coming towards him.

22:13.080 --> 22:16.846
Those ancient men
he knew so well.

22:17.040 --> 22:22.206
He contemplated them, no,
he recognised them silent.

22:22.960 --> 22:24.803
Then a smile,

22:25.000 --> 22:27.571
an amazing smile
stretched his lips

22:27.760 --> 22:29.967
and enlightened his eyes.

22:30.160 --> 22:33.960
That smile was enigmatic because

22:34.160 --> 22:37.403
it was so human, that
it came from the mind.

22:37.600 --> 22:43.050
the continuity between me and them,
and back between them and me,

22:43.240 --> 22:49.930
breaks: I'm a shape whose
knowledge is illusion.

23:27.480 --> 23:30.370
There's the list of the
interviews for Salim.

23:42.280 --> 23:44.123
About the movie release,

23:44.320 --> 23:46.368
Mr Agnelli wants to release
it in Milan first.

23:46.560 --> 23:48.449
He believes that we
will have better odds

23:48.640 --> 23:50.324
with the censorship.

23:50.520 --> 23:53.603
Let's hope he's right.

23:53.800 --> 23:56.280
Some optimism...
Would you like this?

23:56.480 --> 23:57.561
Let me try it.

23:59.640 --> 24:03.042
Aunt Susanna, this was
sent me by Gaetano

24:03.240 --> 24:05.447
Perusini, only for Pier Paolo.

24:05.640 --> 24:07.642
Ah, from Rocca Bernarda.

24:07.840 --> 24:09.683
Is there.. Furio Colombo too?

24:09.880 --> 24:11.530
Yes. It's for la Stampa,

24:11.720 --> 24:14.087
for their new literary section.

24:14.280 --> 24:15.691
But they want to make
it as soon as they can.

24:15.880 --> 24:18.486
Ask him if he can come
by this afternoon.

24:24.400 --> 24:25.367
Now, Graziella,

24:25.560 --> 24:26.846
where have you been
these last days?

24:27.040 --> 24:29.281
We've been to the pinewood
in Castel Fusano.

24:29.480 --> 24:32.131
A beautiful place. Full
of beautiful flowers.

24:33.080 --> 24:36.562
And what about you? E'
piaciuta Stoccolma Pieruti?

24:36.760 --> 24:39.445
Yes mommy, but I think
we would never be able

24:39.640 --> 24:41.847
to live there, you and I...

24:44.000 --> 24:46.367
And what do you think
about Montale's Nobel?

24:46.560 --> 24:50.724
I said at Stockholm that

24:50.920 --> 24:53.127
they should have given it to
Sandro Penna, and not to Montale.

24:53.320 --> 24:56.608
By the way how's Sandro doing?

24:56.800 --> 24:58.882
Did you see him lately?

24:59.080 --> 25:02.323
Sandro is poor and sick...

25:02.520 --> 25:05.603
now he's complaining since he
isn't able to chew anymore.

25:05.800 --> 25:08.371
I don't get why he doesn't
want to use a denture...

25:08.560 --> 25:12.360
now he has this bad habit of calling
on the phone here at night..

25:12.560 --> 25:14.642
And he talks, and
talks, and talks..

25:14.840 --> 25:17.650
Last time, aunt
Susanna put the phone

25:17.840 --> 25:19.842
on the table and she went
back watching the TV...

25:20.800 --> 25:25.249
You should write down
everything he says, instead.

25:25.440 --> 25:26.521
He is a great poet.

25:32.480 --> 25:33.641
It's Laura.

25:37.720 --> 25:38.926
Here she is...

25:48.280 --> 25:50.328
- Hi, Graziella!
- Hello Laura.

25:52.560 --> 25:54.005
How do you do?

25:54.200 --> 25:55.122
Very well. What about you?

25:55.320 --> 25:56.162
Welcome back Laura.

25:56.360 --> 25:57.122
Handsome.

26:01.800 --> 26:03.370
Good morning!

26:03.560 --> 26:04.561
Hello.

26:04.760 --> 26:06.091
Susanna...

26:06.360 --> 26:07.282
How's it going?

26:07.480 --> 26:08.242
Well, well.

26:08.440 --> 26:09.646
What about you?

26:09.840 --> 26:11.683
Get me a chair.

26:14.800 --> 26:16.245
How was your travelling?

26:16.440 --> 26:18.408
Fine, fine. What about yours?

26:18.600 --> 26:20.602
Zagabria... your Jancso pal

26:20.800 --> 26:23.371
tortured us for the whole movie

26:23.560 --> 26:26.040
we shot without a break

26:26.240 --> 26:29.050
these last two days,
all day and all night.

26:29.240 --> 26:31.049
It was madness, mom.

26:31.240 --> 26:34.687
And did you manage to
give him what he wanted?

26:34.880 --> 26:36.530
Of course.

26:36.720 --> 26:38.643
In the beginning he tried to

26:38.840 --> 26:39.568
stop me from improvising

26:39.760 --> 26:43.367
but in the end... I've helped him
shooting the orgy sequences...

26:43.560 --> 26:46.450
Ah socialist actresses

26:46.640 --> 26:48.085
such a wonder, eh...

26:48.280 --> 26:51.204
I adore them, they're
real professionals!

26:51.400 --> 26:53.482
They put this hemorrhoids cream

26:53.680 --> 26:55.364
on their pussies to
hide the wrinkles..

26:56.640 --> 26:58.210
I'll start putting it too.

26:58.400 --> 27:01.961
But here... on the
eye wrinkles, look!

27:02.160 --> 27:04.686
Since I don't have the money for

27:04.880 --> 27:08.123
expensive creams... Oh, so good!

27:08.320 --> 27:09.287
Are you hungry?

27:09.480 --> 27:13.804
No, but you can't imagine how much I
missed the Italian food in Jugoslavia,

27:14.000 --> 27:17.129
because there the food is awful

27:17.320 --> 27:20.369
I don't know why communism and
fine cuisine are always apart...

27:20.560 --> 27:26.567
Ah, I brought you something that...
well...

27:26.760 --> 27:28.000
I hope you like.

27:28.200 --> 27:30.362
Croatian Folkloristic Music.

27:30.560 --> 27:31.721
Ah, thanks.

27:31.920 --> 27:32.921
And I've brought something
for the girls too...

27:37.320 --> 27:38.321
Thanks

27:38.520 --> 27:42.320
You're welcome. And Susanna...

27:42.520 --> 27:43.646
Oh, you're so sweet.

27:48.960 --> 27:51.406
We didn't have this one.

27:53.240 --> 27:54.207
May I?

27:54.400 --> 27:55.162
Of course.

27:58.240 --> 27:59.526
Some wine?

27:59.720 --> 28:01.131
Yes, I'd like some..

28:05.040 --> 28:08.283
Ah... you can put
your jewels there.

28:09.800 --> 28:11.928
Is it true Laura that you
dubbed the Devil's voice?

28:12.640 --> 28:15.610
Yes, Graziella, I've
worked under the Devil..

28:15.800 --> 28:18.007
The Hollywood cinema...

28:18.200 --> 28:22.603
Help somebody who served
the Church, father.

28:32.680 --> 28:38.767
Oh.. Oh honey come here and let
me show you how communists dance,

28:38.960 --> 28:39.643
They dance,

28:39.840 --> 28:41.808
and they even dance well, look..

28:42.000 --> 28:46.767
Here you go, this way,

28:56.240 --> 28:57.127
Take it...

28:59.640 --> 29:01.130
Graziella... you should

29:01.320 --> 29:02.162
use more make-up

29:02.360 --> 29:03.725
you're so pretty..

29:03.920 --> 29:06.161
Come on Graziella, dance
with me some more...

29:12.640 --> 29:14.369
Here...

31:25.520 --> 31:26.806
Good evening.

31:27.000 --> 31:28.729
Good evening. Here.

31:29.840 --> 31:30.762
Good evening.

31:30.960 --> 31:32.405
Good evening, make
yourself at home.

31:32.600 --> 31:33.249
Thanks

31:42.240 --> 31:43.401
May I offer you some coffee?

31:43.600 --> 31:44.840
No thanks, water is just fine.

31:45.040 --> 31:45.404
How do you do?

31:45.600 --> 31:48.080
Well. Take a sit.

31:56.240 --> 31:57.651
Let's get started right away...

32:00.120 --> 32:02.646
So... In what you have written,

32:02.840 --> 32:05.286
in your articles, you gave
many versions of what you hate

32:05.480 --> 32:08.643
and therefore you have opened
a fight against institutions,

32:08.840 --> 32:12.686
ideologies, powers, and
against some people,

32:12.880 --> 32:15.645
now to make our conversation a
little bit less complicated

32:15.840 --> 32:19.526
I'll call all of this "the
situation", but it's clear

32:19.720 --> 32:23.008
that I'm referring to that scene
you usually speak against.

32:23.200 --> 32:25.248
But I want to make
this consideration,

32:25.440 --> 32:29.286
let's put that you
have a magical mind,

32:29.480 --> 32:33.371
you move your hand and
everything disappears,

32:33.560 --> 32:34.925
everything you hate.

32:35.120 --> 32:39.444
You are then alone, alone and
with no means whatsoever,

32:39.640 --> 32:40.926
with no expressive means I mean.

32:43.480 --> 32:45.608
Yes, I get it, oh,

32:45.800 --> 32:47.609
you're talking about
a magical mind...

32:47.800 --> 32:52.044
which not only I'm looking for but
which I also believe in, not because

32:52.240 --> 32:54.891
I think myself as a wizard,

32:55.080 --> 32:57.731
but because I know that
by hitting the same

32:57.920 --> 32:59.570
nail even a house can collapse.

32:59.760 --> 33:02.923
Those who made history

33:03.120 --> 33:05.327
were not the courtesans and
the cardinals' assistants

33:05.520 --> 33:07.284
but those who were
able to say "no".

33:07.480 --> 33:10.643
Refusal has always been an
essential gesture and therefore

33:10.840 --> 33:12.763
to work it needs to be

33:12.960 --> 33:15.042
great, absolute, and absurd.

33:15.240 --> 33:18.642
Common sense has never
stopped the <<situation>>.

33:19.400 --> 33:22.051
Now, we have three points:

33:22.240 --> 33:23.810
what is "the situation"

33:24.000 --> 33:26.765
why we should stop it
or even destroy it

33:26.960 --> 33:28.200
and how.

33:30.200 --> 33:35.491
Good, now explain
"the situation".

33:35.680 --> 33:38.843
You perfectly know
that what you write,

33:39.040 --> 33:43.648
and your language
have the effect of

33:43.840 --> 33:45.888
sunlight going through the dust.

33:46.080 --> 33:49.402
That is a beautiful picture
but it is hard to understand.

33:49.600 --> 33:53.047
Thank you for the
sun metaphor, but I

33:53.240 --> 33:55.607
want a lot less.

33:55.800 --> 33:58.246
I just want

33:58.440 --> 34:01.125
that you notice this tragedy.

34:01.320 --> 34:02.367
What is this tragedy?

34:02.560 --> 34:05.006
The tragedy is that there are no

34:05.200 --> 34:09.205
human beings anymore, there are only weird
cars crashing one against the other.

34:09.400 --> 34:11.607
And this tragedy started

34:11.800 --> 34:13.643
with that universal

34:13.840 --> 34:14.966
compulsory

34:15.159 --> 34:18.004
and perverse educational
system that shapes all of us,

34:18.199 --> 34:20.202
from the manager class,

34:20.400 --> 34:21.242
down to the poor.

34:21.440 --> 34:25.126
that pushes all of us
inside the arena of having

34:25.320 --> 34:26.764
everything at any cost.

34:26.960 --> 34:27.768
This is the reason

34:27.960 --> 34:29.803
why everyone wants
the same things and

34:30.000 --> 34:30.887
why they behave
all the same way.

34:31.080 --> 34:34.208
So if I have in my hands
an administration

34:34.400 --> 34:37.529
meeting or a financial
maneuver, I use those.

34:37.719 --> 34:40.007
Or I use a crowbar.

34:40.199 --> 34:42.328
And when I decide
to use a crowbar

34:42.520 --> 34:45.330
I make my violence
to get what I want.

34:45.520 --> 34:46.760
Why do I want it?

34:46.960 --> 34:48.803
Because they told me that
it's a virtue to want it.

34:49.000 --> 34:50.922
I exercise the right
to my virtue.

34:51.120 --> 34:53.282
I am a murderer, and
I am a good person.

34:53.480 --> 34:58.725
So people nowadays don't
mind killing at all..

34:58.920 --> 35:02.242
That's where the
scenery has changed,

35:02.440 --> 35:03.726
